  <h4>Duo Points</h4>
  <p>
    If you play a Duo match with a full Duo, you get the point value shown above divided by two.
  </p>
  <p>
    Example: You and your teamate place 1<sup>st</sup>. You get 50 place points.
  </p>
  <p>You are essentially dividing the points evenly.</p>
  <h5>Soloing a Duo</h5>
  <p>
    If you decide to "solo" a Duo match, your placement points will increase considerably. You will receive the original point value PLUS the point value times two.
  </p>
  <p>
    Example: You place 1<sup>st</sup> in a Duo match while "soloing". You get 50 points PLUS (50 * 2) = 150 points.
  </p>
  <h4>Squad Points</h4>
  <p>
    If you play a Squad match with a full Squad, you get the point value shown above divided by four.
  </p>
  <p>
    Example: You and a full squad place 1<sup>st</sup>. You get 25 place points.
  </p>
  <p>Again, you are essentially dividing the points evenly.</p>
  <h5>No-Fill Squad</h5>
  <p>
    If you decide to play a Squad match with less than a full squad, your placement points will increase considerably. You will receive the original point value PLUS the point value times 2.4 TIMES the number of players missing.
  </p>
  <p>
    Example: You place 1<sup>st</sup> in a Squad match with only two players. You get 25 points PLUS (25 * 2.4 * 2) = 145 points.
  </p>
  <p>
    For winning a Squad match while "soloing", you get 205 points.
  </p>
